sentences: Estelle Klein (1930-2004) was an advocate and supporter of folk music in Canada and held numerous influential positions with cultural and heritage organizations during her lengthy career.
Klein was born in Buffalo, New York and moved to Toronto, Canada with her parents in 1933.
During the early 1950s Klein worked at Settlement House in Toronto.
Klein became the artistic director for the Mariposa Folk Festival from 1964,and remained in the position until 1980.
